category: LATIN PHRASES
category comment: 

clue: Lapsus linguae, a sudden, unfortunate utterance, translates to this 4-word phrase

response: a slip of the tongue

clue: Said at funerals, requiescat in pace translates to this

response: rest in peace

clue: Agnus Dei is this 4-legged animal "of God"

response: lamb

clue: In utero means "within the womb"; this other phrase describes something that happens "in glass"

response: in vitro

clue: i.e. is short for this, meaning "that is"

response: id est

